1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,140
Today, we have a little bit of a different kind of guest.

2
00:00:02,440 --> 00:00:15,000
She spent 10 years as a top influencer in the MAGA world, helping to elect Donald Trump, served as a brand ambassador for Turning Point USA, was a political commentator, and is maybe most well known for having a child with the world's richest man, Elon Musk.

3
00:00:15,160 --> 00:00:18,220
And now she has turned her back on all of them and has been telling all.

4
00:00:18,880 --> 00:00:20,820
Ashley St. Clair, welcome to Haley on the Go.

5
00:00:21,620 --> 00:00:23,480
Hey, everyone, welcome back to Haley on the Go.

6
00:00:23,580 --> 00:00:24,160
This is Haley.

7
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:29,240
This is your weekly podcast where we talk to the people you care most about, about the issues that matter most to you.

8
00:00:29,720 --> 00:00:33,200
Make sure to follow and subscribe wherever you get your podcasts to never miss an episode.

9
00:00:33,880 --> 00:00:35,360
Episodes drop every single Thursday.

10
00:00:35,860 --> 00:00:36,900
Let's dive right in.

11
00:00:37,680 --> 00:00:38,700
Hello, hello, Haley.

12
00:00:39,080 --> 00:00:44,640
Is this what the kids call like frame-mogging because you are in stark contrast to me right now?

13
00:00:44,660 --> 00:00:46,220
You look amazing as well.

14
00:00:46,220 --> 00:00:50,200
You look so wonderful and put together and I'm in a hoodie here, but thank you for having me, Haley.

15
00:00:50,680 --> 00:00:52,280
No, thanks for taking the time.

16
00:00:52,280 --> 00:00:53,560
I really appreciate it.

17
00:00:53,860 --> 00:01:08,360
I think I, like so many people, have been really enamored, I would say, with your public divorce with MAGA and its leadership and the details you have been sharing about its internal coordination, how it develops influencers, share specific talking points.

18
00:01:08,940 --> 00:01:10,940
And I want to dive into all of that with you.

19
00:01:11,060 --> 00:01:11,920
It's so fascinating.

20
00:01:12,580 --> 00:01:25,100
Before we do, I would like to spend a little bit of time talking about you and your journey into this space to help my audience learn more about you and also learn why they should trust you or not trust you.

21
00:01:25,540 --> 00:01:28,000
I think you can be a bit of a polarizing figure.

22
00:01:28,140 --> 00:01:38,260
You spent more than a third of your life sharing some really hateful rhetoric and messages against minority communities, but these are viewpoints that you now publicly have apologized for and said you have immense guilt over.

23
00:01:38,700 --> 00:01:46,100
And I know disavowing these beliefs have come at immense both financial and physical risk for yourself, and we'll talk more about that.

24
00:01:46,420 --> 00:01:53,180
But how did you get to the point of even being a MAGA influencer and sort of the face, a face, for this movement?

25
00:01:53,740 --> 00:01:54,380
Yeah, of course.

26
00:01:54,480 --> 00:01:58,400
I want to start off by prefacing that I'm not looking for anybody to trust me.

27
00:01:58,600 --> 00:02:17,140
I know there's just going to be people who don't, and I'm not, when I speak about these things, I'm not looking to garner now a left-wing audience or get trust, but rather just speak openly and honestly about my own experiences throughout this MAGA, what I believe is a cult, because I did get involved very young.

28
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:27,280
I first got involved in this as a teenager when I first started college at 18 years old and started going to my first turning point events at 19, 20 years old.

29
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:42,560
And when you're that age and you have, you're supposed to be forming your own identity and being independent and you're out of the house for the first time, and you're getting swept up in this, this new sense of identity and you have all of these followers and these high up figures.

30
00:02:42,720 --> 00:02:49,080
It was very quickly that I was pulled into and in the same room with Charlie Kirk and all of these figures who are then kind of molding you.

31
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:56,980
I still have the texts of Charlie going through my Twitter page and saying, hey, maybe post this or go this direction, don't do this.

32
00:02:57,460 --> 00:03:08,280
And so it was, it all happened very, very quickly while I'm in college and simultaneously doing beer bongs and then having Charlie, you know, guide me on what to say.

33
00:03:08,340 --> 00:03:16,100
And I'm going to these events and I'm a special guest and I'm like a micro e-celeb within the MAGA world.

34
00:03:16,940 --> 00:03:20,320
And it just kind of snowballed.

35
00:03:20,540 --> 00:03:30,100
Something people need to understand about the pathologies of cults and the structure, the architecture of cults is that it was a lot more than just my political opinions.

36
00:03:30,100 --> 00:03:40,300
Those were very much shaped by older men I dated, older men who were influencing me and my own need for validation and acceptance as a young girl.

37
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:40,820
Yeah.

38
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:45,980
But the structure of this cult is that you are also dependent on them financially.

39
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:58,280
For me to leave was not just for me to change my political beliefs, but to blow my entire life up, to lose all career opportunities, what little I had of it left.

40
00:03:58,880 --> 00:04:02,940
But it wasn't as simple as just leaving.

41
00:04:03,420 --> 00:04:09,180
And so I'm hoping to give people a more nuanced view into what that experience was.

42
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:20,440
And I know that's also going to be detrimental to me because if I am just going to sit here, I could have a very nice career if I just sat here and denounced MAGA and now I'm this left-wing advisor.

43
00:04:20,940 --> 00:04:36,500
But rather I want to tell people where I went wrong and the places where I should have spoke up that I didn't, the places that I chose material comfort over doing what was right and why some people make those decisions.

44
00:04:37,540 --> 00:04:43,880
And I think it's tremendous to use your voice that way because it's a cautionary tale that a lot of people need to hear.

45
00:04:44,020 --> 00:04:55,220
You were so young and being exposed to beliefs, to power, to affirmation, to money is something really hard at a young age to have the ability to turn away from.

46
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:58,120
So it's important that we're sharing these stories.

47
00:04:58,380 --> 00:05:07,420
We're talking about what's happening because so much of life right now exists on the internet and people turn to the internet for comfort, for community, for all of these things.

48
00:05:07,960 --> 00:05:09,560
So I appreciate that.

49
00:05:09,980 --> 00:05:25,260
There is a deep question, and I know you touched upon you're not looking for people to trust you, which I think that is a good perspective to have, although I think you've been very honest about your experiences, is there is a deep question around the grift.

50
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:29,140
And you've exposed sort of some of the pay-to-play and we'll dive deeper into that.

51
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:41,200
But how much of the push and pull of like, do I leave, do I stay was the money versus genuine beliefs that you had?

52
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:47,600
And during the time period, even before you were considering leaving, how much of it was the opportunity versus the belief system?

53
00:05:48,460 --> 00:06:00,020
It's kind of both because there are moments where you question things and then you have these older, more respectable figures who kind of pull you back in and say, here's why you shouldn't divert from these ideologies.

54
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:01,220
Here's why you're wrong.

55
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:08,480
And simultaneously, leaving is really scary because my most recent child was not my first child.

56
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:10,940
I had my older son in 2021.

57
00:06:11,700 --> 00:06:18,900
So to leave that was to destroy my ability to feed my son, to have a roof over our head.

58
00:06:19,180 --> 00:06:27,720
And again, I don't say any of this to excuse the behavior, but rather to shine a light on why some people don't leave sooner.

59
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:34,920
It's really difficult because at this point I had and still have one of the worst digital footprints imaginable.

60
00:06:35,860 --> 00:06:50,340
So it's very hard to go get a job at Starbucks or Pinterest when you have this digital footprint that is so horrific and you have things that are hateful towards groups of co-workers you might have as a barista.

61
00:06:50,620 --> 00:06:55,240
It's not as simple as, oh, well, why don't you just tumble yourself and flip burgers?

62
00:06:55,420 --> 00:06:59,760
They don't even want me to flip burgers when I'm saying the things that I was.

63
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:10,780
And so it is really, really difficult to leave that environment when you have said the things that you have.

64
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:28,520
And not to excuse anything that anyone says at any age, but the internet really awards that kind of extremism content and fuels views, likes, engagement, especially certain platforms based off of how extreme you are on either side.

65
00:07:28,640 --> 00:07:34,660
And so as you start to see that kind of reward, it's easy to go probably push yourself deeper and deeper.

66
00:07:34,660 --> 00:07:41,360
Well, it's much more than just, I don't like when people frame it as just the likes and the dopamine, which it is, right?

67
00:07:41,420 --> 00:07:43,820
They design these social media platforms like slot machines.

68
00:07:43,820 --> 00:08:00,060
You slide it and you get the dopamine hit from your notifications, but it's also a feedback loop of affirmation for what you're saying, for your ideologies where you have, it doesn't matter if this person agrees with me because I have 5,000 people who agree with me and some of the top figures.

69
00:08:00,460 --> 00:08:09,620
So it's also this feedback loop of affirmation of your own opinions, as well as what is really pertinent throughout MAGA.

70
00:08:09,740 --> 00:08:13,780
One of the first things they did was they cut off your access to information, right?

71
00:08:13,860 --> 00:08:16,540
They tell you to distrust your professors.

72
00:08:16,860 --> 00:08:22,400
They had the professor watch list where you're always listening to make sure, ooh, this professor can now be content.

73
00:08:22,580 --> 00:08:23,980
I can report this professor.

74
00:08:24,640 --> 00:08:25,620
Distrust the news.

75
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:26,500
It's fake news.

76
00:08:26,660 --> 00:08:29,460
Trust nothing except truth social and Twitter.

77
00:08:30,060 --> 00:08:32,400
So your access to information is cut off.

78
00:08:32,580 --> 00:08:39,620
And then your only information is this feedback loop from people who are affirming these really bad ideas.

79
00:08:39,919 --> 00:08:44,360
So in the moment, it doesn't feel like you're doing something hateful.

80
00:08:44,660 --> 00:08:52,760
And for me, it took me stepping back to really see the gravity of the harm that I had caused and the hatefulness of a lot of that rhetoric.

81
00:08:52,760 --> 00:08:59,800
Because in the moment, you're being affirmed that this is the strong and mighty path and that you're a part of a good movement.

82
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:07,060
I'm not sure how into philosophy you are, but when you look back on it, it's like Thrasymachus yelling at Socrates that might is right.

83
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:11,920
And that is very much the pathology of MAGA that they pull you into.

84
00:09:13,060 --> 00:09:17,620
And what you said about sort of removing your pathways to knowledge is so true.

85
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:26,100
And it goes beyond the proliferation of the concept of fake news, but even goes so far as to say you shouldn't trust science.

86
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:28,500
You shouldn't trust subject matter experts.

87
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:30,980
So we're seeing that and the impact.

88
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:36,320
It's also they want you to ignore the larger structure of things, especially as it relates to capitalism.

89
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:42,440
They want you to believe that if you have socialist beliefs, then socialists don't have any nice things.

90
00:09:42,440 --> 00:09:44,080
And that couldn't be further from the truth, right?

91
00:09:44,140 --> 00:09:53,360
Or they want you to ignore CRT or critical race theory because that does expose the larger structure of capitalism and what's happening now.

92
00:09:53,460 --> 00:10:02,680
They don't want you to know that the Silicon Valley bros and the men on Wall Street would be very proficient in plantation accounting because it's the same language.

93
00:10:02,960 --> 00:10:09,880
And so they really, this is why they have the war on the Department of Education and this access to information.

94
00:10:10,980 --> 00:10:11,500
100%.

95
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:16,840
And one of the people who controls a platform and a lot of this information is Elon Musk.

96
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:21,760
He is a father to 13 children that we know of with a bunch of different partners.

97
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:25,320
You had a child with him and now are engaged in a custody battle.

98
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:32,320
So I know you may not be able to answer questions about him, but I would like to talk a little bit about it and maybe answer what you can.

99
00:10:32,480 --> 00:10:34,020
And if not, we will move on.

100
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:43,580
But you had a child with Elon in September of 2024, which was peak election season, about two months ahead of November.

101
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:46,460
And he was instrumental in helping get Trump elected.

102
00:10:46,620 --> 00:10:54,860
Elon Musk spent approximately $288 million to support Donald Trump, making him the top individual donor in the country.

103
00:10:55,740 --> 00:10:59,840
What was it like being in contact with him during that time?

104
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:07,860
And to the extent that you were in contact or exposed to him, what is your opinion on why he was so invested in making sure Trump was president?

105
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:16,520
I, you know, again, I'm not at liberty to discuss a lot of items related to this as much as I would like to.

106
00:11:16,920 --> 00:11:31,200
But I think people need to understand that any of these tech bros surrounding Donald Trump during the inauguration are not doing this out of altruism or actual convictions, but rather because they're getting something out of it.

107
00:11:31,740 --> 00:11:38,060
These Silicon Valley tech oligarchs are the most self-interested people in the world.

108
00:11:38,340 --> 00:11:42,340
Okay, you want to talk about gold diggers, nobody has dug more gold than them.

109
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:46,000
They're at the top of the list for digging the most gold and extracting the most resources.

110
00:11:46,820 --> 00:11:51,740
So people really need to understand what's happening, especially with our social media platforms.

111
00:11:52,180 --> 00:11:59,200
And I've described social media and AI at times as kind of the final terrain of extraction for capitalism.

112
00:11:59,580 --> 00:12:07,640
And they are really doing this last pillage on what I believe is our consciousness and our souls, because there's, they don't have as much labor to extract.

113
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:09,900
And so now they're extracting us.

114
00:12:09,900 --> 00:12:18,160
And I think people need to be very invested in their own data rights and their own rights to their personhood.

115
00:12:19,520 --> 00:12:28,440
And I talk a lot on this platform and on my pages about AI and the dangers that they pose, especially to women, which we will talk more about, because I know that you have had experiences with it.

116
00:12:28,780 --> 00:12:42,720
But I did want to ask a little bit more during Trump and Elon sort of public fallout last year, you were already estranged or publicly feuding with Elon and you tweeted, hey, at real Donald Trump, let me know if you need any breakup advice, which was funny.

117
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:51,540
So I have to ask how you knowing both of them, personally, to some extent, do you think they're actually broken up?

118
00:12:51,580 --> 00:12:53,340
Or was that sort of a ruse or distraction?

119
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:56,040
I'm not sure.

120
00:12:56,160 --> 00:12:57,360
I don't know the details.

121
00:12:57,360 --> 00:13:00,920
So I'm kind of against hypothesizing about it too much.

122
00:13:00,920 --> 00:13:05,280
But what I would say is these are both very, they're very similar.

123
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:08,620
So two bulls in a China shop doesn't really work.

124
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:10,280
Okay, very fair.

125
00:13:10,420 --> 00:13:10,960
Good insight.

126
00:13:11,280 --> 00:13:14,520
My last Elon question and we'll move on because I want to learn more about you.

127
00:13:14,640 --> 00:13:19,720
Your journey is we know Elon's on a mission to repopulate the world.

128
00:13:19,860 --> 00:13:23,220
He's even gone so far as to say he would donate his sperm to people.

129
00:13:23,960 --> 00:13:32,500
And there are rumors that he has purchased his own compound or cold in Austin to ask all his baby mamas to live there.

130
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:34,940
Can you confirm or deny if that's a real thing?

131
00:13:35,380 --> 00:13:38,920
I cannot speak about it.

132
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:40,180
It's totally okay.

133
00:13:40,280 --> 00:13:42,340
I understand the intrigue.

134
00:13:43,120 --> 00:13:55,640
No, I had to ask because I do find it really intriguing that a party that is sort of based on family values has so many people so closely related to them that does not display those sort quote unquote traditional values.

135
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:56,680
No, but they will.

136
00:13:57,220 --> 00:13:59,840
They will place them on women, right?

137
00:14:00,020 --> 00:14:05,740
So I was the one who was at the receiving end of Oh, you single mom whore, this and that.

138
00:14:06,020 --> 00:14:14,680
When this news broke, the one the onus for family values was primarily placed on me, and not the man in that situation.

139
00:14:15,280 --> 00:14:31,220
So I, that is, I think, really common in society, whether it's MAGA or not, just placing this sort of unfair, unequal standard on women, on women of color, and just holding them above where we hold men.

140
00:14:31,520 --> 00:14:36,260
And I want to dive deeper into your experiences with MAGA and what you've sort of exposed on social media.

141
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:49,160
Before we do that, last year, you publicly sold your Tesla for money and said that was because Elon Musk cut your son's child support payments by 60% as punishment for disobedience.

142
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:56,160
And this is something I know you cannot comment on, but has sort of been wildly reported on as a tactic of his.

143
00:14:56,780 --> 00:15:06,940
So just before we dive in, what would you say to the people now who sort of question like you were in it for the money, and then the way that they say it are not in for the money, but money opportunities.

144
00:15:07,020 --> 00:15:10,520
And then as sort of people say, the leopard ate your face.

145
00:15:10,780 --> 00:15:12,640
And now you're like reverse grifting.

146
00:15:12,780 --> 00:15:14,520
What would your response to be those people?

147
00:15:15,180 --> 00:15:19,560
Well, first of all, I'm not at liberty to discuss anything involving custody for obvious reasons.

148
00:15:20,020 --> 00:15:24,580
But there is a large cohort who is saying, oh, she's grifting now.

149
00:15:24,660 --> 00:15:26,360
I'm not making any money off of this.

150
00:15:26,620 --> 00:15:31,440
I've turned down enough money to be like the GDP of a small nation at this point.

151
00:15:31,920 --> 00:15:34,520
I'm back in school with plans to go to law school.

152
00:15:34,760 --> 00:15:38,520
I'm not putting TikTok shoplinks on my get ready with me's.

153
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:52,320
And even since coming out against MAGA, I have received offers from center left and left leaning organizations to be a paid spokesperson on TV and basically say what I'm saying now, but be paid.

154
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:58,220
And I've declined that because I think I need to right the wrongs of my past.

155
00:15:58,380 --> 00:16:03,600
And I don't want to be paid for what's coming out of my mouth anymore.

156
00:16:04,020 --> 00:16:18,000
I want to rebuild an actual career and go back to school and go to law school and hopefully do effective advocacy work within the system that I think is responsible for a lot of this harm.

157
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:19,740
And I respect that.

158
00:16:19,860 --> 00:16:27,000
And I truly do believe that we have to create a space for people to be able to change their minds, to grow, to learn.

159
00:16:27,080 --> 00:16:28,740
You were so young when you were exposed.

160
00:16:28,940 --> 00:16:37,400
And if we don't allow people to publicly change their minds, then we will never advance and move away from where we are right now.

161
00:16:37,580 --> 00:16:48,520
So I am grateful that you're speaking out against both where your viewpoints were at one time, but also the system that helped created it.

162
00:16:49,000 --> 00:17:00,960
And I will say too, you know, there's obviously there were things that I did for money that were not okay, specifically as it relates to these paid influencer campaigns.

163
00:17:01,820 --> 00:17:16,359
However, I also think there's a piece of that that ignores the abusive financial coercion that happens within these structures of cults like MAGA or any other cult where that is necessary for so many people.

164
00:17:16,560 --> 00:17:18,280
And again, it does not excuse it.

165
00:17:18,700 --> 00:17:23,400
However, this structure is incredibly deliberate to keep people involved.

166
00:17:24,520 --> 00:17:35,300
And they, to my understanding or knowledge, oftentimes do kind of pry off of young people who are in need of financial support or assistance or security in that way.

167
00:17:36,100 --> 00:17:43,680
So yeah, I don't know that there's any more vulnerable, you know, malleable brain than young college kids or young students.

168
00:17:43,820 --> 00:17:51,960
Now they're going into high schools with turning point and saying, you know, you don't need school, just work for us, just be a professional MAGA spokesperson.

169
00:17:53,340 --> 00:18:02,420
That's incredibly predatory, especially when you're staring down student loan debt, about economy, you know, security is so key.

170
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:11,600
You have been opening up about sort of the way that MAGA has helped mold young people's voices and the experiences within.

171
00:18:12,240 --> 00:18:17,140
Can you talk a little bit about what coordination you saw and experienced?

172
00:18:17,940 --> 00:18:21,800
There were different levers and facets of coordination.

173
00:18:22,240 --> 00:18:28,420
As I had mentioned in, you know, previous appearances that I've done, they have a lot of paid campaigns.

174
00:18:28,760 --> 00:18:40,240
So these influencers are paid just to put out messaging, to put links out to news sites, and they don't have to disclose any of this because of our current FEC regulations and loopholes.

175
00:18:40,340 --> 00:18:44,740
They do not have to disclose anything that's not really like a product, a good, or a service.

176
00:18:45,140 --> 00:18:48,740
And so they are able to do a lot of this coordinated messaging.

177
00:18:49,200 --> 00:19:05,960
There's also these coordinated group chats and campaign calls and calls with the Trump team that I was on, in which they really direct the messaging and say, hey, here's how we respond to this, or don't respond to this, and put out those talking points that way.

178
00:19:06,600 --> 00:19:28,820
And then there's also a more undiscussed is that once some of these big figureheads are given the talking points, it puts the rest of the micro influencers in line to get that social media engagement because they're like, oh, maybe I'll get a retweet from, you know, the big guy or what have you.

179
00:19:29,460 --> 00:19:40,500
So while it's coordinated and they're paid and there's facets of this that are coordinated, it then trickles down to get the rest of the MAGA influencer base in line.

180
00:19:41,360 --> 00:19:51,620
And I think that this coordination is something that people on the left suspected was happening for a long time, but didn't 100% know necessarily that it was.

181
00:19:51,820 --> 00:19:57,440
Are you able to quantify at all some of those payment numbers you have seen?

